== Sessoku-sha (Subordinate Shrines) == * Kusamoto Jinja * Futamine Jinja * Inari Jinja – Enshrined deities: {{ill|Kurainetama-no-Mikoto|ja|倉稲魂命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurainetama-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ウカノミタマ|1=Ukanomitama|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3080728}}, {{ill|Ichikishima-hime|ja|市杵島姫命|1=Ichikishima-hime|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima-hime|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima-hime|qq=||1=Ichikishima-hime|2=fr|3=Ichikishimahime|4=ja|5=イチキシマヒメ|6=zh|7=市寸島比賣命|8=ru|9=Итикишима-химэ|10=de|11=Ichikishima-hime}}, and {{ill|Mizuhayome|ja|水速女命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizuhayome|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ミヅハノメ|1=Mizuhanome|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q8191796}}<ref>Subordinate shrines are recorded based on the shrine’s own historical documents.</ref> * Ushio Jinja – Enshrined deities: [[:en:Oyamakui no Kami|Ōyamakuzume-no-Kami]], {{ill|Aratama|ja|荒魂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aratama|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 荒魂・和魂|1=mitama|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q495568}}, and {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane公|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. * No Jinja – Enshrined deity unknown. * Jishu Jinja – Enshrined deity: {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmononushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大物主}}. (Relocated and enshrined in the shrine grounds in [[:en:1909|1909]], the 42nd year of the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] era.) * Reikōsha – Enshrines the spirits of members of the Yagi family associated with the shrine, as well as the war dead from the [[:en:First Sino-Japanese War|First Sino-Japanese War]], [[:en:Russo-Japanese War|Russo-Japanese War]], [[:en:Second Sino-Japanese War|Second Sino-Japanese War]], and the [[:en:Pacific War|Pacific War]].
== Local Information == '''Location''' * [[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]] [[:en:Ōtsu|Ōtsu City]] Ogoto 2-chōme 10-1
'''Access''' * Rail ** {{ill|JR West|ja|JR西日本|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/JR West|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 西日本旅客鉄道|1=West Japan Railway Company|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q502125}} [[:en:Kosei Line|Kosei Line]]: [[:en:Ogoto-onsen Station|Ogoto Onsen Station]] (approximately 10 minutes on foot) * Bus ** From [[:en:Biwako-Hamaōtsu Station|Biwako Hama Ōtsu Station]] (served by [[:en:Keihan Electric Railway|Keihan Electric Railway]] on the [[:en:Keihan Ishiyama Sakamoto Line|Keihan Ishiyama-Sakamoto Line]] / [[:en:Keihan Keishin Line|Keihan Keishin Line]]), take an Ewaki Bus to the “Kita Ogoto” bus stop (approximately 7 minutes on foot after alighting)
'''Surroundings''' * Fukuryōji – Former [[:en:Jingū-ji|Jingūji]]. The principal image is a seated [[:en:Amitābha|Amida Nyorai]] by Ennin, designated as an Important Cultural Property.
